<item>
            <title>[LU-18286] tests: auster node.yml labels rocky9 as RHEL</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18286</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve tried to search in Maloo for any results of b_es6_0 client with Rocky9.x distribution and got nothing but several failed node-provisioning. Meanwhile Yu Jian pointed out to some sessions with Rocky9 clients:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/d6acb4b8-9653-462d-9ad5-e04f6f547b5b&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/d6acb4b8-9653-462d-9ad5-e04f6f547b5b&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#65532;&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/447310ef-dc22-491f-843f-6a213d75774e&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/447310ef-dc22-491f-843f-6a213d75774e&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In both clients are reported as &apos;RHEL9.4&apos; and that is why search by Rocky9.x distribution doesn&apos;t work it seems. So Rocky9.x distributions are not reported correctly in Maloo for some reason.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;btw, &apos;Rocky8.x&apos; reported quite well&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
