                            <comment id="429792" author="leonel8a" created="Tue, 1 Oct 2024 17:24:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This requires a change in lustre-release, opened &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18287&quot; title=&quot;Update yaml.sh&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18287&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-18287&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, patch submitted&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="429784" author="colmstea" created="Tue, 1 Oct 2024 16:49:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The node data in Maloo comes from lustre/tests/yaml.sh.&#160;release() in yaml.sh is incorrectly labeling rocky9 nodes as RHEL 9&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;-bash-4.4# lsb_release -d
Description: &#160;Rocky Linux release 8.8 (Green Obsidian)
-bash-4.4# . /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/yaml.sh
-bash-4.4# release
Rocky 8.8&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;-bash-5.1# lsb_release -d
Description: &#160;Rocky Linux 9.4 (Blue Onyx)
-bash-5.1# . /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/yaml.sh
-bash-5.1# release
RHEL 9.4&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
